public enum EngineThresholds
extends Enum<EngineThresholds>

An enum whose members can be used to set query options with Double values, representing thresholds which can be overridden to tune CQEngine query performance.

If a threshold is not set as a query option, a default threshold will be applied. Note that default thresholds might change between CQEngine versions.

Author:
niall.gallagher

Enum Constant Detail

INDEX_ORDERING_SELECTIVITY

public static final EngineThresholds INDEX_ORDERING_SELECTIVITY
A threshold between 0.0 and 1.0, which refers to the selectivity of the query which triggers CQEngine to use an index to order results, instead of retrieving all results and ordering them afterwards.

There is a trade-off between these strategies, because index ordering forces use of a particular index whereas that index might not always be the most optimal to quickly locate objects which match the query. On the other hand if the query matches a large number of results then sorting those results afterwards can be relatively expensive. Hence this threshold, which refers to the point at which CQEngine will automatically choose one of these strategies over the other for each particular query.

CQEngine calculates the selectivity of the query roughly as:
1.0 - [number of objects the query matches]/[number of objects in the collection]
Therefore a query with low selectivity matches most of the collection, and a query with high selectivity matches a small number of objects in the collection.

When CQEngine determines that the selectivity of the query is lower than this configured threshold, then it will use an index to order results. When query selectivity is higher than this threshold then it will retrieve all results and order them afterwards.
